## 🔍 SEO — MANDATORY RULES

**Every component, page, and section must be built with SEO in mind from the first line.**

### HTML Semantics (Non-Negotiable)
- Use semantic HTML5 elements: `<header>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<nav>`, `<aside>`
- Every `<section>` must have an `aria-label` or `aria-labelledby` attribute
- One `<h1>` per page — place it in the Hero section, never repeat it
- Heading hierarchy must be strictly sequential: h1 → h2 → h3 (never skip levels)
- Never use headings for visual styling — use CSS instead
- All interactive elements must have accessible labels (`aria-label`, `title`, or visible text)
- All images must have meaningful `alt` attributes (descriptive, not keyword-stuffed)
- Decorative images: `alt=""` and `aria-hidden="true"`

### Meta & Head Management
- Use `react-helmet-async` (or `@vitejs/plugin-react` + `<Helmet>`) for dynamic `<head>` management
- Every page must define: `<title>`, `<meta name="description">`, canonical URL
- Title format: `Page Name | Na Kawkę` — max 60 characters
- Description: unique per page, 120–155 characters, include primary keyword naturally
- Open Graph tags required on every page: `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:image`, `og:url`, `og:type`
- Twitter Card tags: `twitter:card`, `twitter:title`, `twitter:description`, `twitter:image`
- All OG images: 1200×630px, under 300KB

### Structured Data (JSON-LD)
- Implement `LocalBusiness` schema on the homepage
- Implement `FAQPage` schema if an FAQ section exists
- Implement `Product` schema on package detail pages (Standard, Premium)
- Place `<script type="application/ld+json">` inside `<Helmet>` or in a `StructuredData` utility component
- Validate with Google Rich Results Test before merging

```tsx
// Example StructuredData utility component
// src/app/components/seo/StructuredData.tsx
import { Helmet } from 'react-helmet-async';

interface StructuredDataProps {
  schema: Record<string, unknown>;
}

export const StructuredData = ({ schema }: StructuredDataProps) => (
  <Helmet>
    <script type="application/ld+json">
      {JSON.stringify(schema)}
    </script>
  </Helmet>
);
```

### Sitemap & Robots
- Generate `sitemap.xml` — use `vite-plugin-sitemap` or generate at build time
- `robots.txt` must exist in `public/` and allow all bots
- Every route added to `routes.tsx` must also be added to the sitemap config

### URL & Routing
- URLs must be descriptive and in the language of the target audience (Polish): `/pakiet-standard`, `/pakiet-premium`
- No trailing slashes inconsistency — pick one convention and stick to it
- Canonical tags on all pages to prevent duplicate content

