## ⚡ PAGESPEED / CORE WEB VITALS — MANDATORY RULES

**Target scores: LCP < 2.5s, CLS < 0.1, FID/INP < 200ms. Lighthouse score ≥ 90 on all categories.**

### Images
- **Always** use modern formats: WebP as primary, AVIF where supported. Fallback to JPEG/PNG.
- Implement responsive images with `srcSet` and `sizes` attributes
- Every image must have explicit `width` and `height` attributes to prevent CLS
- Lazy-load all images below the fold: `loading="lazy"` + `decoding="async"`
- Hero/above-the-fold images: `loading="eager"`, `fetchPriority="high"` — never lazy-load them
- Use `<picture>` element for format fallbacks:

```tsx
<picture>
  <source srcSet="image.avif" type="image/avif" />
  <source srcSet="image.webp" type="image/webp" />
  <img
    src="image.jpg"
    alt="Descriptive alt text"
    width={800}
    height={600}
    loading="lazy"
    decoding="async"
  />
</picture>
```

### Fonts
- Self-host fonts in `assets/fonts/` — never load from Google Fonts CDN at runtime
- Use `font-display: swap` in all `@font-face` declarations
- Preload critical fonts in `index.html`:

```html
<link rel="preload" href="/fonts/inter-variable.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin>
```

- Limit font weights to what's actually used — no unused variants

### JavaScript & Code Splitting
- Use dynamic `import()` for all route-level components (lazy loading via React Router)
- Never import heavy libraries (e.g. chart libs, animation) at the top level if only used on one page
- Tree-shake all imports — use named imports, not default namespace imports
- Avoid large third-party scripts in `<head>` — defer or async everything non-critical
- Use `React.memo` for expensive pure components, `useMemo`/`useCallback` where genuinely needed

### CSS & Rendering
- Tailwind's PurgeCSS is active in production — do not generate class names dynamically (string interpolation)
- Avoid `@import` in CSS — use `@layer` and direct `@tailwind` directives
- No render-blocking CSS — critical styles can be inlined in `index.html` if needed
- Avoid large layout shifts: always define container dimensions before content loads (use skeleton loaders)

### Preloading & Resource Hints
- Add to `index.html` for critical resources:

```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://your-pocketbase-domain.com">
<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="https://your-pocketbase-domain.com">
```

### Caching & Build Output
- Configure Vite for long-term asset caching (content hashes in filenames — this is default)
- Static assets in `public/` should be served with long cache headers (configure on host)
- Set `Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable` for all hashed assets

### Performance Checklist (per component)
- [ ] No layout shift introduced (CLS)
- [ ] Images have explicit `width` and `height`
- [ ] Images are lazy-loaded (except above-the-fold)
- [ ] No blocking scripts added
- [ ] No large CSS bundles introduced
- [ ] Animations use `transform` / `opacity` only (GPU-composited layers)

