## 📊 ANALYTICS (UMAMI) — RULES

### Purpose
Umami is used for privacy-friendly analytics (visits, page views) on the production site.

### Implementation
- Analytics script is loaded via the `Analytics` component in `src/app/components/seo/Analytics.tsx`.
- The component is mounted once in `App.tsx` and injects the Umami script into `<head>`.

### Stub when running locally
- **When the project runs locally** (`pnpm dev` / `vite`), the analytics script must **not** run.
- The component checks `import.meta.env.DEV`: if `true` (development), it does not inject the script — no tracking in local/dev environment.
- In production build (`vite build`), `import.meta.env.DEV` is `false` and the script is loaded as usual.
- Do not add the analytics script to `index.html` — it would run in all environments. Keep the conditional injection in the `Analytics` component.

### Script
- URL: `https://umami.digital-office.pl/script.js`
- Website ID is set in `Analytics.tsx` via `data-website-id`. No env var required for the public ID.

