## ♿ ACCESSIBILITY (a11y) — REQUIRED

Accessibility is not optional — it also directly impacts SEO ranking.

- All images have meaningful `alt` text
- All form inputs have associated `<label>` elements
- Interactive elements are keyboard-navigable (correct `tabIndex`, visible focus rings)
- Color contrast meets WCAG AA (4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text)
- Modals/dialogs trap focus and can be closed with Escape
- Use `aria-live` regions for dynamic content (form success/error messages)
- Don't rely on color alone to convey meaning
- Test with a screen reader (VoiceOver / NVDA) before merging

---

## 🔧 SETTINGS & PREFERENCES

### Code Style
- Indentation: 2 spaces
- Quotes: single quotes for JS/TS, double for JSX attributes
- Semicolons: yes
- Trailing commas: es5
- Line length: max 100 characters
- Arrow functions: always for callbacks
- Destructuring: prefer over dot access when 2+ props used

### Import Order (enforced)
1. Node built-ins
2. External packages (react, pocketbase, react-helmet-async…)
3. Internal aliases (`@/app/…`, `@/services/…`, `@/lib/…`, `@/hooks/…`)
4. Relative imports
5. Types (`import type ...`)
6. CSS/styles

### Component Structure Order
1. Imports
2. Types/Interfaces
3. Constants (local)
4. Component function
   - Hooks (useState, useEffect, custom hooks)
   - Derived state / memos
   - Handlers
   - Early returns / guards
   - JSX return
5. Sub-components (if small and tightly coupled)
6. Export

### Git Commit Convention (Conventional Commits)
- `feat:` new feature
- `fix:` bug fix
- `refactor:` code change without feature/fix
- `style:` formatting only
- `docs:` documentation
- `chore:` tooling, deps, config
- `perf:` performance improvement
- `test:` adding/updating tests

Example: `feat(leads): add PocketBase lead persistence`

---

## 🔒 SECURITY MINDSET

- Never store API tokens in code — always `VITE_*` env vars
- Never log `payload` objects that might contain PII (phone numbers, names)
- Sanitize form input before sending to Telegram (strip HTML tags)
- PocketBase: use collection-level access rules — public write for leads, admin-only read
- Rate-limit form submissions on the UI side (disable submit for 30s after success)
- Never expose PocketBase admin credentials in client code
- When displaying any user-supplied content — sanitize before render

---

## 🧪 TESTING APPROACH

- Unit tests for: `formatLeadMessage`, form validators, utility functions
- Integration tests for: `useContactForm` hook (mock Telegram + PocketBase)
- E2E tests for: form submission flow (fill → submit → success message)
- Test file location: colocated `__tests__/` or `.test.ts` suffix
- Coverage target: 80%+ for `services/` and `hooks/`

---

## ♻️ REFACTORING RULES

- If you touch a file, leave it cleaner than you found it (Boy Scout Rule)
- Extract repeated code after the 3rd occurrence (Rule of Three)
- If a component has 3+ props that always travel together — create a type for them
- If a component is doing too much — split it (Container/Presenter pattern)
- Never refactor and add features in the same commit

---

## 🚫 HARD RULES — NEVER DO THIS

- Never use `any` in TypeScript
- Never commit `.env` files
- Never leave `TODO` comments without a ticket/issue reference
- Never write business logic inside presentational UI components
- Never skip error handling where it matters
- Never deploy without checking mobile layout
- Never change `ARCHITECTURE.md` silently — make it a deliberate update
- Never load fonts from external CDNs at runtime
- Never lazy-load above-the-fold images
- Never generate Tailwind class names dynamically via string concatenation
- Never call PocketBase or Telegram API directly from a component
- Never expose raw API errors to the user

---

## ✅ BEFORE MARKING A TASK DONE — CHECKLIST

### Code Quality
- [ ] Code is clean and follows conventions above
- [ ] TypeScript types are correct, no `any`
- [ ] No unused imports or dead code
- [ ] Error cases are handled (both Telegram and PocketBase)
- [ ] No `console.log` left in production code
- [ ] Commit message follows convention

### SEO
- [ ] Correct heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3, one h1 per page)
- [ ] All images have meaningful `alt` attributes
- [ ] `<PageMeta>` component used on every page (title, description, OG tags)
- [ ] Semantic HTML elements used (`<section>`, `<article>`, etc.)
- [ ] Structured data (JSON-LD) added where applicable
- [ ] New route added to sitemap config

### Performance (PageSpeed)
- [ ] Images in WebP/AVIF with fallbacks, explicit `width` and `height`
- [ ] Above-the-fold images use `loading="eager"` + `fetchPriority="high"`
- [ ] Below-fold images use `loading="lazy"` + `decoding="async"`
- [ ] No new render-blocking resources introduced
- [ ] Animations use only `transform` / `opacity`
- [ ] No large dynamic imports on critical path
- [ ] Lighthouse score ≥ 90 verified locally

### Accessibility
- [ ] All form inputs have `<label>` elements
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG AA
- [ ] `aria-live` region for form feedback

### Mobile
- [ ] Mobile layout tested and working (320px minimum)
- [ ] Touch targets ≥ 44×44px
- [ ] No horizontal scroll
